45 guidance relating to best practices for secure browsing and parental controls. The
46 Department of Education shall provide technical assistance in addition to such model
47 programs and recommended curricula and instructional materials to aid any local board
48 of education that may elect to incorporate one or more components of internet and social
49 media safety into its instructional program.
50 (5) The Department of Education shall evaluate the report published by the Attorney
51 General pursuant to subsection (g) of Code Section 39-5-5 in assessing the reach and
52 impact of online safety education efforts.
53 (b) Each local board of education may incorporate into its instructional program a
54 component on online internet safety, including social media safety, to be taught on a
55 schedule as determined by the local board of education."
56 SECTION 2.
57 Chapter 5 of Title 39 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to online internet
58 safety, is amended by adding a new subsection to Code Section 39-5-5, relating to
59 commercial entity age verification, access to material harmful to minors, data retention,
60 penalties, and exclusions, to read as follows:
61 "(g) The Attorney General shall publish an annual report documenting enforcement actions
62 taken under this Code section."
63 SECTION 3.
64 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
